Title : Mount Jacobsen
Text : '''Mount Jacobsen''', 3031 m (9944 feet),<ref>[http://bivouac.com/MtnPg.asp?MtnId=1987 Bivouac Mountain Encyclopedia entry]</ref> is a [[mountain]] in the northernmost [[Pacific Ranges]] of the [[Coast Mountains]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], located to the south of the [[Bella Coola Valley]] and immediately south of [[Ape Lake]], to the west of the valley of the [[Talchako River]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/9571.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Mount Jacobsen"]</ref>  

The [[Noeick River]] begins at the '''Noeick Glacier''' on the northwest side of the peak at {{coord|52|06|00|N|126|16|00|W|display=inline|source:BCNames}}.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16968.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Noeick Glacier"]</ref>  In the same [[massif]] and immediately west of the peak of Mount Jacobsen is '''West Jacobsen Peak''', 2971 m (9747 feet)<ref>[http://bivouac.com/MtnPg.asp?MtnId=5865 Bivouac Mountain Encyclopedia entry]</ref> at {{coord|52|03|25|N|126|12|09|W|display=inline|source:BCNames}}.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16968.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Noeick Glacier"]</ref><ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16970.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Noeick River"]</ref>  '''Ape Glacier''', named in association with [[Ape Lake]] and [[Ape Mountain]], is on the north side of the Jacobsen massif.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/2112.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Ape Glacier"]</ref> at {{coord|52|05|00|N|126|12|00|W|display=inline|source:BCNames}}.

==Name origin==
Mount Jacobsen and West Jacobsen Peak are named for B.F. Jacobsen, who settled in the Bella Coola Valley prior to 1890 and was who encouraged the Reverend [[Christian Saugstad]], the namesake of [[Mount Saugstad]], to move his colony of Norwegian immigrants to Bella Coola from [[Minnesota]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17162.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Mount Saugstad"]</ref>

